dc_title_s: A general map of the empire of Germany, Holland, the Netherlands, Switzerland, the Grisons, Italy, Sicily, Corsica, and Sardinia
dc_description_s: Cartographic Details: Scale [1:530,000] All maps are double except number 4, 13, and 16. Unnumbered frontispiece is an index map which is duplicated in number 13 and 16. Number 23 is an engraved title page. Index map signed: S.J. Neele, sculpt.|25 [i.e. 26] leaves of plates : all maps ; 66 x 50 cm.|Scale [1:530,000]|General Map Collection
